text:
Today we released our latest State of Crypto report.

It shares insights on key trends — like stablecoins, L2s, and AI — plus, crypto’s rise as a policy issue, new data on builders and users, and more.

7 takeaways from the report:

1. Crypto activity and usage hit all-time highs

2. Crypto has become a key political issue ahead of the U.S. election

3. Stablecoins have found product-market fit

4. Major scaling upgrades have drastically reduced onchain transaction costs

5. DeFi remains popular — and it’s growing

6. Crypto could solve some of AI’s most pressing challenges

7. More scalable infrastructure has unlocked new onchain applications

Read the full report here: https://a16zcrypto.com/posts/article/state-of-crypto-report-2024/

text:
very delayed, but very excited to publish the vibe check with @adrienne and @nounishprof we did for their 1 year anniversary :)

https://pods.media/vibe-check/vibe-check-12-nounishprof-and-adrienne-gmfarcaster

transparently, i've been struggling with vibe check.  With FC growing and cozy corners proliferating, my original idea for an FC coded GTM podcast doesn't seem to make sense anymore.  So officially, the pod will go on hiatus while I decide the new direction.

i have the deepest appreciation and gratitude to all my guests who've come on so far, and excited to see what I can dream up as the next iteration/season 2 of the pod.  Definitely more to come - eventually :)

thanks again to the /gmfarcaster hosts for coming on the show with me, I can think of a better way to cap off the first season of this experiment. We'll be back better than ever with some new ideas once I feel confident that they're ready to be tested in the wild

wuf out <3

show_title: GM Farcaster ep170 Friday October 18, 2024 with guest @burrrrrberry
text:
So let me preface this with "your coin; your rules" so this all certainly your call @betashop.eth re: /moxie but this seems a bit hasty. I've found that carrots tend to work better than sticks. 

So regarding this "we feel that $250 in rewards is a generous amount after which to require everyone to play in the system in order to continue earning," which on its face isn't unreasonable except some people have actually put in funds to support the experiment but are likely being swept up into this. 

No idea where I am in regards to rewards and haven't received this notice yet BUT I couldn't actually claim my airdrop when moxie first launched so I put in 1 eth of my own funds so that I could support the project and buy some fan tokens etc. 

(continued in replies)
